Yes — you start with the database first, but not alone. You start with the CORE SYSTEM FOUNDATION, not features.
Here is the correct production-grade build order for Bushmarket (strict sequence):
🧱 1. SYSTEM FOUNDATION (DO THIS FIRST)
👉 This is where everything depends on.
You build:
Project structure (FastAPI backend)
Environment config (.env)
PostgreSQL connection
Base ORM setup (SQLAlchemy Base)
Migration system (Alembic)
Redis connection (for events + cache)
Kafka connection (event bus skeleton)
✔ Without this → nothing else is real
🗄️ 2. DATABASE DESIGN (VERY IMPORTANT NEXT)
Yes — database comes early.
You design tables for:
users (existing system assumed)
cooperatives
memberships
cooperative_wallets (later financial_core)
events log table (optional but powerful)
✔ This is where your entire system truth lives
🔐 3. AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM (COOKIE-BASED LIKE FACEBOOK)
Before business logic.
Build:
Login system
JWT or session cookies (HttpOnly secure cookies)
Refresh token system
Middleware auth guard
✔ Every feature depends on identity
🧠 4. CORE DOMAIN (COOPERATIVE ENGINE — YOUR CURRENT WORK)
Now build what you already started:
Build in order:
Cooperative creation
Membership join logic
Cooperative lifecycle (draft → active → funded → closed)
Product targeting rules
Duplicate prevention logic
✔ This is your business brain
💰 5. FINANCIAL CORE (MOST CRITICAL SYSTEM)
Do NOT skip or fake this.
Build:
Ledger system (PostgreSQL double-entry)
Escrow wallet
Contribution tracking
Refund system
Payment gateway integration (Paystack/Stripe)
✔ This makes system REAL MONEY-READY
📡 6. EVENT BUS SYSTEM (REAL-TIME ENGINE)
Now connect everything.
Build:
Kafka event publisher
Event consumers
Redis pub/sub for fast updates
Events like:
member_joined
payment_success
funding_reached
order_started
✔ This powers EVERYTHING live
🔔 7. NOTIFICATION SYSTEM
Build:
SMS (Termii / Twilio)
Email (SMTP / SendGrid)
Push notifications (Firebase)
✔ Triggered by event bus
🛒 8. MARKETPLACE + SUPPLIER INTEGRATION
Build:
Product catalog
Supplier APIs
Bulk order engine
Pricing logic for cooperative buying
📦 9. ORDER + DELIVERY SYSTEM
Build:
Order creation
Shipment tracking
Delivery status updates
Logistics integration
📊 10. DASHBOARD SYSTEM
Build:
Cooperative progress tracking
Funding percentage
Member analytics
Financial transparency
📱 11. FLUTTER APP (LAST FRONTEND)
Only AFTER backend is stable.
Build:
API integration
Auth login
Cooperative UI
Wallet UI
Live updates (WebSocket / polling)
🚀 12. DEPLOYMENT (RAILWAY)
Final step:
Dockerize backend
Add CI/CD
Env config
Deploy API + workers + Kafka consumers
⚠️ CRITICAL RULE (MOST IMPORTANT)
If you break order, system will fail:
❌ Do NOT build Flutter first
❌ Do NOT build payment first
❌ Do NOT build notifications first
✔ Always follow:
Foundation → Database → Auth → Core Domain → Finance → Events → Notifications → Marketplace → Delivery → UI → Deployment
🧠 SIMPLE SUMMARY (ONE LINE)
👉 You first build infrastructure + database + auth, then cooperative logic, then money system, then event-driven systems, then frontend.
